---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 4
title: About
description: sysf.io is an independent Swiss sovereign-AI engineering studio. We build custom fine-tuned models on Apertus and ship them end-to-end — so regulated organizations can adopt AI without giving up control of their data.
---
{% from "partials/components.njk" import sectionHead, cta %}

<section class="border-b border-ink-900/10 dark:border-white/10">
  <div class="container-x py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-4xl font-bold leading-[1.08] tracking-tightest text-ink-900 md:text-5xl dark:text-white">
      Sovereign AI shouldn't mean second-best AI.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg prose-muted md:text-xl">
      sysf.io exists to give regulated organizations a way to adopt AI on their own terms — private, compliant, and genuinely their own — without settling for a locked-down black box in someone else's datacentre.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Mission -->
<section class="container-x py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12">
    <div class="md:col-span-5">{{ sectionHead("Why we exist", "The sovereignty gap.") }}</div>
    <div class="md:col-span-6 md:col-start-7 space-y-5 text-lg prose-muted">
      <p>The most capable AI has, until recently, lived behind closed US APIs. For a Swiss bank, a hospital or a cantonal authority, that's a dead end: the data can't leave, so the pilot dies.</p>
      <p>Switzerland answered with <a class="link-underline" href="{{ site.baseModel.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apertus</a> — a fully open, sovereign, multilingual model from EPFL, ETH Zurich and CSCS, with open weights and documented training data. It closes the capability gap while keeping everything inspectable and ownable.</p>
      <p>Does a fine-tuned open model actually hold up? The public evidence says yes: the <a class="link-underline" href="https://www.cscs.ch/science/computer-science-hpc/2026/apertus-powers-in-house-ai-translation-for-ticino" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Canton of Ticino's translation service</a> reached <strong class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">94% accuracy after fine-tuning Apertus-8B</strong> on cantonal data — a model that knows your documents beats a bigger one that has never seen them.</p>
      <p>sysf.io is an independent Swiss engineering studio that turns that open foundation into working systems. We do the hard part — fine-tuning, retrieval, evaluation, compliance documentation and operations — so you get a system you own, measured on your task, running where your data already lives.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Principles -->
<section class="border-y border-ink-900/10 bg-ink-900/[0.02] py-20 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-white/[0.02] md:py-28">
  <div class="container-x">
    {{ sectionHead("Principles", "How we work.") }}
    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
      {% set vals = [
        {t:"Sovereignty first", d:"Your data and your model stay in your jurisdiction and your control. Always."},
        {t:"Open over closed", d:"We build on open weights so you get transparency, auditability and no lock-in."},
        {t:"Products, not demos", d:"We measure success by what runs in production, not by what impresses in a meeting."},
        {t:"Compliance by design", d:"Regulatory fit is engineered in from step one — not retrofitted before launch."}
      ] %}
      {% for v in vals %}
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ v.t }}</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm prose-muted">{{ v.d }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Differentiation -->
<section class="container-x py-20 md:py-28">
  {{ sectionHead("What makes us different", "Three ways to get sovereign AI — and what you actually receive.") }}
  <div class="mt-12 overflow-x-auto">
    <table class="w-full min-w-[720px] border-collapse text-sm">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b border-ink-900/15 text-left dark:border-white/15">
          <th class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white"></th>
          <th class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-swiss">sysf.io (studio)</th>
          <th class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink-500">Sovereign platform (hosted endpoint)</th>
          <th class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink-500">US cloud API (Swiss region)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-ink-900/10 dark:divide-white/10">
        {% set rows = [
          {k:"Where data lives", a:"Your infrastructure — on-prem, your tenancy, or air-gapped", b:"The provider's Swiss datacentre", c:"Provider's region, under US legal reach"},
          {k:"Model weights", a:"Open, fine-tuned on your corpus, auditable", b:"Shared base model, open or closed", c:"Closed, opaque"},
          {k:"Who builds your product", a:"We do — scoped use case, eval plan, delivery", b:"Your team, on their endpoint", c:"Your team, on their API"},
          {k:"Accuracy on your task", a:"Measured against your eval set before go-live", b:"Unknown until you build and test", c:"Unknown until you build and test"},
          {k:"Ownership & exit", a:"You own the model; handover is a deliverable", b:"Subscription — access ends with the contract", c:"Rented access"},
          {k:"Compliance documentation", a:"Delivered with the system", b:"Platform-level; use-case compliance is yours", c:"Shared responsibility — mostly yours"}
        ] %}
        {% for r in rows %}
        <tr>
          <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-medium text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ r.k }}</td>
          <td class="py-4 pr-4 text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300">{{ r.a }}</td>
          <td class="py-4 pr-4 text-ink-500">{{ r.b }}</td>
          <td class="py-4 pr-4 text-ink-500">{{ r.c }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-sm text-ink-500">To be fair to the alternatives: a managed platform is the right answer if you have an AI engineering team and want infrastructure only, and a US cloud API is the right answer if your data can leave. We're the answer when the data can't leave and you want the system built, measured and handed over.</p>
</section>

{{ cta("Work with us.", "If sovereignty, compliance and ownership matter to your AI roadmap, we should talk.") }}
